OL,3,C'Significant changes and improvements'
OL,4,Cmade to hospital since Letby's attacks
OL,6,FShe said: "You can have all the
OL,7,Fpolicies and processes in the world
OL,8,Fbut unless people feel accountable for
OL,9,Ffollowing them then they will never be
OL,10,Feffective.
OL,12,F"From what I have read it feels like
OL,13,Flip service was paid to the Speak Out
OL,14,FSafely policy, that there was a
OL,15,Fculture of fear, that the board was
OL,16,Fdominated by the views of a number of
OL,17,Findividuals, it was not a unitary
OL,18,Fboard, and people were potentially
OL,19,Fthreatened with punitive action if
OL,20,Fthey didn't toe a particular line."
OL,26,@nD@KOUtD@AOU|D@cO]
